Data Cleaning

In [ ]:
cleaned_data = rental[(rental.price != 0) & (rental.num_baths >= 0) 
                    & (rental.num_beds > 0) & (rental.sqft > 0) & (rental.PopulationDensity > 0) & (rental.ac)].dropna().copy()

Here we use around 87K lines with nan values.

7. cluster the data with square feet, baths, bedrooms, population density

In [ ]:
from sklearn.decomposition import PCA
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
from sklearn.metrics import silhouette_score
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans
In [ ]:
feats_ = ["log_sqft", "num_beds", "num_baths", "PopulationDensity"]
X = ohe_cleaned_data[feats_]
scalar = StandardScaler()
data = scalar.fit_transform(X)
In [ ]:
pca = PCA(n_components=2).fit(data)
data2d = pca.transform(data)

plt.figure(figsize=(16, 8))
scores, n_clusters, preds = [], [], []
for i in range(2, 10):
    kmean = KMeans(n_clusters = i, random_state=22).fit(data)
    scores.append(kmean.score(data))
    n_clusters.append(i)
    pred = kmean.predict(data)
    preds.append(pred)
    plt.subplot(2, 4, i - 1)
    plt.title(f"{i} clusters silhoute={np.round(silhouette_score(data, pred), decimals=5)}")
    plt.scatter(x=data2d[:, 0], y=data2d[:, 1], c=pred, cmap=plt.cm.OrRd, marker = '.')
    
    centroids = kmean.cluster_centers_
    centroids2d = pca.transform(centroids)
    plt.plot(centroids2d[:, 0], centroids2d[:, 1], 'b+', markersize=15)
plt.savefig("sihoute.png")

In [ ]:
from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeRegressor
from sklearn.model_selection import cross_validate
from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error
In [ ]:
def err_func(regressor, x, y):
    y_pred = np.exp(regressor.predict(x))
    y_true = np.exp(y)
    return mean_squared_error(y_true, y_pred)
In [ ]:
feats_ = ["log_sqft", "num_beds", "num_baths", "PopulationDensity"]
X = ohe_cleaned_data[feats_]

scalar = StandardScaler()
data = scalar.fit_transform(X)
In [ ]:
regressor = DecisionTreeRegressor(max_depth=3, min_samples_leaf=0.01)
scores = cross_validate(
    estimator=regressor, 
    X=data, y=y, cv=5, 
    scoring=err_func, 
    return_train_score=True,
    return_estimator=True
)
print(pd.DataFrame(scores))
